prompt:
Add a public function called ReadInput to Effects.calr that reads a line from the console and returns it. It takes no parameters and returns str. The function must declare the console read effect.

Use this exact Calor console read syntax:
§F{f001:ReadInput:pub}
  §O{str}
  §E{cr}
  §B{input} §C{Console.ReadLine}§/C
  §R input
§/F{f001}

The §E{cr} declares the console read effect:
- cr = console read (Console.ReadLine, Console.Read, etc.)
- This effect indicates the function reads from stdin
- Must be declared for any console input operations
